Rating: 0
The secret ingredient to a good Bolognese is chicken livers. I know this scares Americans, but you won't taste the livers, and will get the flavor depth and color that you're looking for. Use about half the amount of the other meats. Also, use veal, so: 1 lb beef, 1/2 lb veal, l/b pork, 1/4 lb chicken livers. (Adjust other amounts as sensible.) Beef stock is very important, you can replace some of the tomato juice. Garlic doesn't help if you follow these suggestions, it will conflict with the livers - but then again not every Italian recipe needs garlic :-)

