Rating: 3
Ok - it's VERY close to a traditional bolognese sauce EXCEPT it should have beef/meat stock (1.5 C) added over the course of the cooking, should start with about 4T of chopped mortadella (or proscuitto) added after the veggies, before the meat, and should DEFINITELY be cooked for approximately 5 hours. I also add veal to the pork/beef mixture. For those of you who left out the nutmeg, it's crucial. It doesn't taste like nutmeg, but is necessary for flavor depth. Also, bolognese almost NEVER has garlic, basil, etc. in it - that just makes it an excellent meat ragu! For those of you who ended up with hamburger soup, that's lack of cooking I think (per the instructions) - and I PROMISE the nutmeg makes a difference!

