I took this recipe, bearing in mind that bolognese is SUPPOSED to be a relatively mild meat ragu, and added a few things according to some of the previous reviewers comments. First, I started with more aromatics than the recipe called for, all chopped very fine. Then I added a little lemon zest, fresh rosemary and fresh thyme, salt, pepper, and 1 tsp. sugar. Next I included some ground lamb in the meat mixture. Then I deglazed with 1.5 cups of red wine, before adding pureed tomatoes and a little beef broth. Reduce for 1.5 hours, add 3/4 cup cream, reduce 20-30 minutes further, stir in a handful of parmesean or peccorino and serve. It was good, but next time I'll use even more ground lamb in the recipe, but most importantly, I will make the sauce a day ahead.

