My husband said this is one of his favorites and I love it too. I've made it several times combining some of the other suggestions along with one of my own. The changes I make are substituting half and half for the milk, draining after cooking the meat and using red wine (Cabernet) instead of white.

Rating: 2
I've had more flavorful bolognese sauce so this was a little dissapointing. Big on filling comfort food over gnocchi but lacking in taste...needs ALOT of spicing up.

Rating: 4
Delicious. I improvised by adding mushrooms, garlic, a little sugar and threw a small jar of Prego into the sauce to help thicken it. I also drained the grease from the meat before the step of adding the milk to the sauce.

Rating: 2
I was disappointed in the recipe. My suggestions for the future: Cut down the fat that you cook the meat in by at least half - the sauce got way too greasy. I used red wine and thought it really overpowered the whole taste - I would cut down on the wine, or eliminate it all together next time.

Rating: 3
This is a great winter sauce. Perfect for cold evenings when you want something hearty. Great with a big glass of red wine! I used Italian sausage insteads of the pork and used half and half instead of milk. I would definitely make it again!

Rating: 3
This sauce is wonderful! It has become the sauce I use with my lasagna rolls. It is also economical.

